London Riots Prompt Cameron to Recall Parliament as Extra Police Called In

-- B y   E d d i e   B u c k l e
-- 
2011-08-09T10:08:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/london-riots-prompt-cameron-to-recall-parliament-as-extra-police-called-in.html
Prime Minister  David Cameron  recalled
Parliament from its summer vacation after police made more than
200 arrests in a third night of rioting in  London  and unrest
spread to other British cities.  The prime minister, speaking outside his Downing Street
office in London, summoned an emergency session of the House of
Commons for Aug. 11.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Eddie Buckle at 
 ebuckle@bloomberg.net  